                                <h1 style="font-family: 'Archivo Black', sans-serif; margin: 0; padding: 0;">CLAIMS</h1>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    Claims allow you to protect your land from other players.
                                </p>

                                <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
                                    There are three types of fortification materials: Stone, Iron and Diamond.
                                </p>

                                <p><b>Stone:</b> Matures in 10 minutes, adds 100 durability to the block.</p>
                                <p><b>Iron:</b> Matures in 1 hour, adds 500 durability to the block.</p>
                                <p><b>Diamond:</b> Matures in 6 hours, adds 1800 durability to the block.</p>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0; color: red!important;"><b>REMEMBER!</b></p>
                                <p>All blocks can be broken <i>eventually</i>. Each time a fortified block is broken it loses 1 durability. Once it reaches 0, the block breaks and drops the fortification material.</p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
                                    <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/gM_DY06aQ40" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
                                </div>

                                <h5 style="margin-top: 8px;">Commands</h5>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/claim info</kbd> - Enter INFO mode, right-click to view a Claim</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/claim materials</kbd> - View a list of valid fortification materials</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/claim fortify &lt;network&gt;</kbd> - Begin fortifying every block you place with the fortification material you're currently holding</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/claim reinforce &lt;network&gt;</kbd> - Begin reinforcing every block you punch with the foritifcation material you're currently holding</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/claim disable</kbd> - Leave any claiming modes you're currently in</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/claim help</kbd> - View a list of these commands in-game</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="factory" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <img src="/images/factory.png" style="max-width: 100%;">
                                <h1 style="font-family: 'Archivo Black', sans-serif; margin: 0; padding: 0;">FACTORIES</h1>

                                <p>
                                    <b>Note:</b> The furnace needs to be in the middle.
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                    Factories allow you to mass produce resources. Think of them as much fancier Furnaces.
                                    To create a Factory, place a Crafting Bench, Furnace and Chest all next to each other.
                                </p>

                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0;">
                                     Once you've placed the blocks type
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                     <kbd>/factory create &lt;network&gt;</kbd> to initialize it.
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                    Once the Factory has been created, right-click the Crafting Bench to access a GUI containing
                                    every possible Factory Recipe. When you hover over a Recipe you will notice they show a list of
                                    <b>Input Resources</b> and <b>Output Resources</b> along with a <b>Time</b> and <b>Experience Reward</b>.
                                </p>

                                <img src="/images/factory-example.jpg" style="max-width: 100%; margin-bottom: 16px;">

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;"><b>Input Resources</b></p>
                                <p>This is what you have to pay. Upon clicking this recipe the items will be subtracted from your inventory and the job will start.</p>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;"><b>Output Resources</b></p>
                                <p>This is what you will receive. These items will be automatically placed in the Chest.</p>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;"><b>Time</b></p>
                                <p>This is the amount of time it is going to take to run this job.</p>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;"><b>Experience Reward</b></p>
                                <p>As your Factory completes jobs this number will go towards the EXP level of the Factory. As the Factory levels up you will earn access to more recipes.</p>

                                <p>
                                    Once you have selected a job and it is running, you can monitor it by right-clicking the Furnace.
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                    <b>Note:</b> You can run up to 9 jobs per Factory.
                                </p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
                                    <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/l-2ey60apUY" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
                                </div>

                                <h5 style="margin-top: 8px;">Commands</h5>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/factory create &lt;network&gt;</kbd> - Create a factory</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/factory recipes</kbd> - Open a GUI containing every possible recipe</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

