                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="prisonpearl" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <img src="/images/prisonpearl.png" style="max-width: 100%;">
                                <h1 style="font-family: 'Archivo Black', sans-serif; margin: 0; padding: 0;">PRISON PEARL</h1>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    When a player is slain by someone who has at least 1 Enderpearl in their hotbar the player will be
                                    imprisoned within that Enderpearl for up to 14 days. From here, it is up to the killing player to hold
                                    their Prison Pearl and transport it to a location to store it.
                                </p>

                                <br>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    When you are Prison Pearled, you are still allowed to join the server but you can <b>not</b> leave The End.
                                    The only way you can be set free before 14 days is to be released by another player. You can find the most
                                    up-to-date location of your Prison Pearl by typing <kbd>/pp locate</kbd>
                                </p>

                                <br>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    <b>Note:</b> You can locate any players Prison Pearl by typing
                                </p>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    <kbd>/pp locate [username]</kbd>
                                </p>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">This can be extremely handy if you are trying to locate a hidden base.</p>

                                <br>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    It is <b>highly</b> recommended to only store Prison Pearls in heavily protected areas. Any player can locate a Prison Pearl you're holding
                                    and come raid your base. Sometimes, it may be better to let someone free.
                                </p>

                                <br>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">
                                    If you do find yourself Prison Pearled you can find out how much longer your imprisonment is by typing <kbd>/pp info</kbd>
                                </p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <h5>Commands</h5>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/pp locate</kbd> - View your Prison Pearl's current location</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/pp locate [username]</kbd> - View an imprisoned player's Prison Pearl location</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/pp mute</kbd> - Mute location updates for your Prison Pearl</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/pp info</kbd> - View your imprisonment information</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="world" role="tabpanel">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <img src="/images/world.png" style="max-width: 100%;">
                                <h1 style="font-family: 'Archivo Black', sans-serif; margin: 0; padding: 0;">THE ARES WORLD</h1>

                                <p style="margin: 0; padding: 0;">The world is a custom-generated 10,000 x 10,000 map with several major changes to the vanilla gameplay. Here is a condensed list:</p>

                                <ul>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">There are no fast-travel methods (Example: /f home)</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Mob Spawners are disabled</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Looting and Fortune enchantments grant bonus experience</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">All ores have been drained from the map and have been replaced by a system which spawns ore veins around you as you mine</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">You can uncover Glowstone and Nether Quartz by breaking Netherrack in The Nether</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Potion values have been reverted back to pre-1.6</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Instant Harming & Poison 2 Potions have been disabled</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Leaving a Minecart with a block directly above it will teleport you to the next highest block above it (Elevators)</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Commonly spawned mobs will "stack". Stacked mobs are indicated by a number over their heads.</li>
                                    <li style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Emeralds can be converted to EXP Bottles</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <h5>Commands</h5>
                                <p style="display: block; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid black; margin-bottom: 8px;">Spawn</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/spawn</kbd> - Randomly spawn in to the map</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/spawn bed</kbd> - Spawn in your bed</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/spawn request &lt;player&gt;</kbd> - <span class="badge badge-info">Premium Only</span> - Request to teleport to a player</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/spawn accept &lt;player&gt;</kbd> - Accept a player's teleport request</p>

                                <p style="display: block; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid black; margin-bottom: 8px;">Combat</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/pvp enable</kbd> - Remove your Prison Pearl Protection</p>

                                <p style="display: block; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid black; margin-bottom: 8px;">Compactors</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/compact</kbd> - Compact every block of the type you're holding to 1 single item. (Costs 5 levels per 64 blocks)</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/decompact</kbd> - Reverts a compacted item back to normal form</p>

                                <p style="display: block; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid black; margin-bottom: 8px;">EXP Bottling</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/bottle</kbd> - <span class="badge badge-info">Premium Only</span> - Place all of your current EXP Levels in a glass bottle</p>

                                <p style="display: block; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: bold; margin: 0; padding: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid black; margin-bottom: 8px;">Settings</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/ares settings</kbd> - Access settings directly related to Ares</p>
                                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem;"><kbd>/settings</kbd> - Access settings across all Ares servers</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
